name: spyder-reports
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "spyder-reports" %}
{% set version = "0.1.1" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash = "30362a96aa1d0eb9e8f09fd3fbfa3b07255e1cf656a80be2b95ee3ae85a0d504" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash }}

build:
  number: 1001
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - spyder >=3.2
    - pweave 0.25  # [py27]
    - pweave  # [py3k]
    - qtpy
    - pandoc
    - matplotlib

test:
  imports:
    # Skip on Posix because it's segfaulting
    - spyder_reports  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/spyder-ide/spyder-reports
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'Spyder-IDE plugin for Markdown reports using Pweave.'
  description: |
    Currently it supports basic functionality such as rendering mdw and md reports,
    and saving them in your filesystem.
  dev_url: https://github.com/spyder-ide/spyder-reports

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ccordoba12
